==English==

===Noun===

# [[tree]] (in a [[graph theory]]), where removal of all end-[[vertex|verteces]] results in a [[path]]. (Chartrand, G., L. Lesniak. Graphs & Digraphs. Chapman & Hall, London, 1996.) Another definition of the same concept says that it is a [[tree]] with a single [[path]] (the spine) that includes or is incident to every edge. (West, Douglas B. . Introduction to Graph Theory. Prentice Hall, Upper Saddle River, 1996.) Yet a third wording says that it is a [[tree]], in which every vertex is on a central stalk or only one graph edge away from the stalk. As a consequence, a tree is a caterpillar if, and only if, all verteces with [[degree]] at least 3 are surrounded by at most two verteces of degree two or greater.
# [[deciduous]] tree growing in Southeastern U.S. (Catalpa bignonioides of family Bignoniaceae, also called Southern Catalpa) which is the host plant for the catawba [[worms]], caterpillars that are popular fishing bait. [http://www.discoverlife.org/ed/tg/images/catalpa_eggs.jpg Leaf of a Caterpillar tree picture]